The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for Alzheimer's disease classification using neurological imaging data, specifically MRI and PET. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning algorithms for classification indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the potential clinical benefits of the research suggest that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
